descriptionNullable:
### Context

There is a big wave in the number of new infections with coronavirus. It is quite difficult to predict this accurately. 
Here, let's try to make predictions in chronological order using the open data set of the Ministry of Health, Labor and Welfare.

### Content

Please refer to the homepage below for each column.


### Acknowledgements

resources used 
https://www.mhlw.go.jp/stf/covid-19/open-data.html


### Inspiration

Step 1 is a task to predict the number of newly infected people in the future from the past data of each prefecture.
In step2, we predict the number of newly infected persons for all past strains of randomly selected prefectures. In this task, you can get the correct answer data from label.csv.
Note that step1 and step2 are composed of exactly the same data, so the data of the other task cannot be used.
